RACE.FOOTNOTES: APACHE took a bump from an inner rival at the start, stalked outside of the top pair, pressed around the turn, bid entering the lane, cleared at the furlong grounds, and held off an outer challenger late. FRISCO LINE settled at the rear two wide, fanned four wide in upper stretch, rallied with a clear APACHE to catch in the final furlong, but was fended off late. GRAND HIDEAWAY broke out and bumped a foe at the start, set the pace inside of a vying rival, got headed at the quarter pole, gave way in the final furlong, and held show between horses late. SAMURAI SAINT raced at the rear along the inside, and improved. RAF was bumped by an inner rival into an outer foe at the start, vied for the lead two wide, led turning for home, but was outkicked by an outer bidder in upper stretch, and weakened between horses at the furlong grounds. CAPTAIN MAD JACK laid off of the pace in the three path, floated to the six path entering the lane, and made little impact. NO BANG NO BOOM (IRE) shied and steadied from an inner rival soon after the start, tracked the top trio from the two path, chased them entering the lane, and faded. HIDING THE BRICK lacked speed in the five path, bore out to the eight path nearing the lane, and tired.
